Full Title: The 5th Postgraduate Research Forum on Linguistics 
Short Title: PRFL-5 2008 

Date: 15-Mar-2008 - 16-Mar-2008
Location: Hong Kong, China 
Contact Person: Jie Guo
Meeting Email: prfl2008@gmail.com
Web Site: http://www.cuhk.edu.hk/lin/conference/prfl/ 

Linguistic Field(s): General Linguistics 

Call Deadline: 15-Dec-2007 

Meeting Description:

The postgraduate research forum is a conference organized by postgraduate
students of linguistics and linguistics-related disciplines in Hong Kong. The
purpose of this event is to provide a platform for research students to
introduce their interests and on-going projects, and to exchange innovative
ideas about linguistic issues. It was previously held every two years from 1997
to 2003. After a five-year suspension, we are honored to resume the event in
2008, and to host it at the Chinese University of Hong Kong for the first time. 

Linguistic Areas:

Syntax and semantics 
Phonetics and phonology 
Language acquisition 
Sociolinguistics 
Sign linguistics 
Language contact and language change 
Psycholinguistics and neurolinguistics 
Computational linguistics 
Important dates:

Abstract submission deadline: December 15, 2007
Notification of Acceptance: From January 20, 2008
Proceeding Paper submission deadline: April 16, 2008


 




